<http://dx.doi.org/10.12933/therya-23-2290>
    dc:creator "Alarcón Cifuentes, Mallerly", "Morales-Martínez, Darwin Manuel", "Noguera-Urbano, Elkin A.", "Ossa-López, Paula A.", "Pérez, Weimar A.", "Ramírez-Chaves, Héctor E.", "Rivera-Páez, Fredy A.", "Torres-Martínez, Maria M." ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Systematics, morphometry, and distribution of Eptesicus fuscus miradorensis (H. Allen, 1866) (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae), with notes on baculum morphology and natural history" ;
    bibo:endPage "311" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Therya" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-05-30" ;
    bibo:startPage "299" ;
    bibo:volume "14" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263454>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263456>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263458>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263460> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263454>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Details of the skull (ICN 17189; female from Department of Santander, Colombia) of E. miradorensis. a. Ventral view. b. Dorsal view. c. Lateral view. d. Alive specimen from Serranía del Perijá, Colombia (ICN uncatalogued) shows long brownish hair and a dark,naked face." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10263454/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263456>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Details of the skeleton (a-b) and baculum (c-e) of Eptesicus miradorensis (QM JM 6365) from México. a.Dorsal view. b.Ventral view. c.Baculum shape and position (green) embedded in the penis (grey structure). d:Dorsal view of the baculum. e.Ventral view of the baculum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10263456/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263458>
    dc:description "Figure 4. PCA plots of (a) cranial and (b) external measurements of Eptesicus miradorensis from different localities along its distribution range." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10263458/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10263460>
    dc:description "Figure 5. a.Suitability map ofEptesicus miradorensis in America using the Maxent algorithm. The higher suitability values are present in México,Guatemala,north Colombia, and Venezuela. b. Binary distribution map of Eptesicus miradorensis using the 10-percentile threshold value. Red points represent the species records." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10263460/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

